      "date": "2013-05-25 07:43:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nThe patch itself looks mostly good. In conf-sanity test_53 the modified line should use a tab and wrap at 80 columns if the patch needs to be refreshed.\n\nIt would be nice if someone looked into checkpatch.pl to see why it does not check the code style for shell scripts?  I thought I saw that it had the ability to do this, but I don't know enough perl to see why it doesn't work. \n\nNote that the extra testing from Test-Parameters failed. Not sure if it relates to the patch or not, but at least this patch does not regress the main review testing (it passed 2/3 review runs, only failing one test on the third).",
